# Cursor Rules for TMQL

## TypeScript Type Checking

**ALWAYS use the project tsconfig.json when checking TypeScript files.**

- ✅ **Correct**: `npx tsc --noEmit --project .` or `bun run build`
- ❌ **Incorrect**: `npx tsc --noEmit src/path/to/file.ts` (ignores tsconfig.json)

When checking individual TypeScript files for type errors, always use `--project .` to ensure the project's tsconfig.json (which extends tsconfig.options.json) is applied. Checking files individually without `--project .` uses default compiler options and may show false errors or miss project-specific settings.

The build command (`bun run build`) correctly uses the project tsconfig, so type assertions that pass in the build may appear to fail when checking individual files without the project flag.
